<paragraph blockId="25.[178,1085,1181,1233]" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name 
<emphasis box="[565,630,1181,1202]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">plauta</emphasis>
is a Greek adjective derived from 
<emphasis box="[994,1054,1181,1202]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="1538">platys</emphasis>
(= flat). I refer to the body form of these beetles.
